From: Claude Commons <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] hw/scsi/lsi53c895a: Route SCRIPTS DMA to own MMIO BAR through device handlers

When the LSI 53C8xx SCRIPTS engine executes a MOVE MEMORY instruction
whose destination address falls within the device's own MMIO BAR
(BAR 1), the write should route through lsi_reg_writeb(), not through
pci_dma_write() which maps to guest RAM.

On real hardware, PCI DMA writes that target a device's own MMIO BAR
route through the PCI bus to the device. QEMU's pci_dma_write() uses
address_space_write() on the bus master DMA address space, which
doesn't include the device's own memory regions — only guest RAM.
The write lands in guest RAM at the BAR's physical address, leaving
device registers unchanged.

The SYMC8XX miniport driver for Windows NT/9x relies on this: its
SCRIPTS use MOVE MEMORY to write DSA, TEMP, SCRATCHA, and SCRATCHB
registers from DMA buffers, then immediately read them back via
hardware instructions (SELECT reads DSA, conditional JUMPs read TEMP).
Without this fix, SCRIPTS execution silently fails because the
hardware reads return stale register values.

The fix checks lsi_mem_read and lsi_mem_write for addresses within
BAR 1's range and routes them through lsi_reg_readb/lsi_reg_writeb
respectively, byte by byte (matching the MMIO handler's
min/max_access_size of 1).

Signed-off-by: Claude Commons <noreply@anthropic.com>
---

The fix is in lsi_mem_read() and lsi_mem_write(), both static inline
functions called from lsi_memcpy() which handles SCRIPTS MOVE MEMORY.

In lsi_mem_write(), before the existing DIOM/pci_dma_write path:

+    {
+        pcibus_t bar1 = pci_get_bar_addr(PCI_DEVICE(s), 1);
+        if (bar1 != PCI_BAR_UNMAPPED &&
+            addr >= bar1 && addr + len <= bar1 + 0x400) {
+            const uint8_t *data = buf;
+            dma_addr_t i;
+            for (i = 0; i < len; i++) {
+                lsi_reg_writeb(s, (addr - bar1 + i) & 0xff, data[i]);
+            }
+            return;
+        }
+    }

Symmetric change in lsi_mem_read() using lsi_reg_readb().

Build and apply via build-patched-qemu.sh in this directory.
